(1, 'BENIN', 'benin', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (8).svg', 'The ECTN of BENIN is a document that is required for all shipments of goods to the Republic of Benin. The ECTN is used to track and control the movement of goods into and out of the country and to ensure that all customs duties and taxes are paid.', 'ECTN Benin | Seanauatic Marine', 'ECTN Benin: The ECTN of BENIN is a document that is required for all shipments of goods to the Republic of Benin. Contact us now. ', 'asset/maps/benin.jpg', 'The ECTN is an export control document. It is required for all goods shipped from the Republic of Benin destined for a port outside of the country. To obtain an ECTN, the exporter must first submit a request to the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Republic of Benin.<br>The request must include:<br>A list of the products to be exported,, The Harmonized System (HS) code for each product,, The value of the goods,, The country of destination,, The port of exit from Benin Once the request is approved by the Chamber of Commerce, the ECTN will be issued,, The ECTN must be attached to the invoice and packing list for the goods. It is valid for one shipment only.', '<b>How do I get an ECTN?</b><br><br>Your shipping company will usually take care of obtaining an ECTN on your behalf. If you are arranging your own shipping, you can apply for an ECTN through the website of the European Union’s Directorate-General for Taxation and Customs Union.<br><br>,,<b>What information do I need to provide to get an ECTN?</b><br><br>To apply for an ECTN, you will need to provide the following information: <br>-Your name and contact information <br>-The name and contact information of the shipper <br>-The name and contact information of the consignee <br>-The port of loading and the port of discharge <br>-The estimated time of departure <br>-The estimated time of arrival <br>-The type of cargo being shipped.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(2, 'BURKINA FASO', 'burkina-faso', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (7).svg', 'The ECTN OF BURKINA FASO, or Entry Clearance Certificate, is required for all travellers to BURKINA FASO. The ECTN must be obtained prior to travel and presented to immigration officials upon arrival in the country. <br><br>\r\n\r\nThe ECTN is obtained through the BURKINA FASO embassy or consulate. As part of the application process, travellers must provide proof of travel plans, hotel reservations, and a return ticket. The embassy or consulate will then issue the ECTN, which must be presented to immigration officials upon arrival in BURKINA FASO. There is a fee for the ECTN, which varies depending on the country of origin.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>For example </b>: The fee for citizens of the United States is $160. The ECTN is valid for one year from the date of issuance and allows for multiple entries into BURKINA FASO.<br><br>\r\n\r\nTravellers must have the ECTN with them at all times while in the country. If you have any questions about the ECTN or the application process, please contact the nearest BURKINA FASO embassy or consulate.', 'ECTN Burkina Faso | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Burkina Faso:The ECTN OF BURKINA FASO, or Entry Clearance Certificate, is required for all travellers to BURKINA FASO. Contact us Now', 'asset/maps/Burkina-faso.jpg', 'Every importer in Burkina Faso must obtain an Etiquette de Cote (ECTN) prior to shipping their products into the country. The ECTN is a document that certifies that the products being shipped have been inspected and meet all the necessary requirements for importation. To obtain an ECTN, the importer must first submit a request to the Directorate General of Customs.<br><br>This request must include:<br>&#x2022; A copy of the commercial invoice <br> &#x2022; A copy of the bill of lading or airway bill <br>&#x2022; A description of the products being shipped <br>&#x2022; The value of the shipment <br>&#x2022; The HS code of the products Once the request is received, the Directorate General of Customs will issue a provisional ECTN. This provisional ECTN is valid for 10 days and allows the importer to make changes to the request if necessary. Once the 10 days have passed, the Directorate General of Customs will issue the final ECTN. This ECTN is valid for 6 months and must be presented to the customs authority at the port of entry when the shipment arrives.', '<b>Who needs an ECTN for Burkina Faso?</b><br>\r\nAny company or individual that is exporting goods from Burkina Faso is required to obtain an ECTN.<br><br>\r\n<b>How do I get an ECTN for Burkina Faso?</b><br>\r\nYour company will need to apply for an ECTN through the Burkinabe Chamber of Commerce and Industry.<br><br>\r\n<b>What information do I need to provide to get an ECTN for Burkina Faso?</b><br>\r\nWhen applying for an ECTN, you will need to provide the following information:<br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of your company <br>\r\n&#x2022; A description of the goods being exported <br>\r\n&#x2022; The value of the goods being exported <br>\r\n&#x2022; The destination of the goods - The date of export.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(3, 'CONGO', 'congo', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (2).svg', 'All shipments of commodities from the Republic of Congo are required to have an ECTN or Export Control Authorization Number. Before export, the ECTN must be obtained from the National Trade Facilitation Committee. <br><br>\r\n\r\nThe ECTN is only good for a year and needs to be renewed every year.', 'ECTN Congo | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Congo: All shipments of commodities from the Republic of Congo are required to have an ECTN or Export Control Authorization Number. ', 'asset/maps/congo.jpg', 'Contact the National Directorate of Customs and Excise to get an ECTN in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (Direction Nationale des Douanes et Accises - DNDA). In Congo, the DNDA is the appropriate institution to issue ECTNs.<br><br><b>Getting an ECTN in Congo involves the following steps:</b><br><br>1. The shipper must provide an ECTN upon the consignee\'s (the importer\'s) request (the exporter’s).<br><br>2. The shipper must request an ECTN from the appropriate agency in their exporting nation (in this case, the DNDA).<br><br>3. The shipper is required to give the consignee the ECTN after it has been granted.<br><br>4. At the Congo port of entry, the consignee must show the ECTN to the customs office.<br><br>All shipments of commodities intended for export in Congo must have an ECTN. The ECTN is a document that attests to the payment of the proper export duties for the cargo. Additionally, it is utilised to trace the package and make sure it securely reaches its destination.', '<b>Who is eligible to utilise ECTN Congo?</b><br><br>All companies in the Republic of Congo are welcome to join the ECTN Congo. However, companies must register and set up a profile in order to use the site.<br><br>,,<b>How much does using the ECTN Congo cost?</b><br><br>The ECTN Congo is a cost-free service. Registration and profile creation for companies are free of charge.<br><br>,,<b>How do companies sign up for the ECTN Congo?</b><br><br>By visiting the website and selecting the \"Register\" option, businesses may sign up for the ECTN Congo. Businesses will have to supply certain fundamental data.', 'The following advice should be kept in mind when utilising an ECTN in Congo:<br><br>1. Verify that the ECTN is appropriate for the route you intend to take.<br><br>2. Before leaving, make sure to provide the carrier with the ECTN.<br><br>3. Ensure that the ECTN is listed in the shipping documents.<br><br>4. Ensure that you retain a copy of the ECTN for your records.', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', 'Exporters can send information on export controls and trade notifications to the government of the Republic of the Congo through the web programme known as ECTN Congo, or the Export Control and Trade Notification service. The service\'s objectives include streamlining the export procedure and giving Congo\'s customs officers the knowledge they need to accurately evaluate and handle export goods.<br><br>The flow of cargo into and out of the nation is tracked using the ECTN Congo, an electronic cargo tracking note. It is necessary for all cargo shipments to and from the Congo. The ECTN Congo is only good for a year and needs to be renewed every year.<br><br>The ECTN Congo, which tracks the flow of cargo into and out of the nation, is good for a year. An ECTN is required for every cargo shipment into and out of the Congo.'),
(4, 'CENTRAL AFRICAN REPUBLIC', 'central-african-republic', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (11).svg', 'An ECTN (Electronic Cargo Tracking Note) is a 10-digit number required for all shipments of goods from the Central African Republic (CAR) to the United States.<br><br>The ECTN is used to track shipments and prevent cargo from being lost or stolen in transit. The ECTN is required for all shipments of goods from the Central African Republic (CAR) to the United States.<br><br>The ECTN is used to track shipments and prevent cargo from being lost or stolen in transit. To obtain an ECTN, shippers must first register with the CAR government and obtain a Shipping Identification Number (SIN). Once the SIN has been obtained, the shipper must apply for an ECTN from the CAR customs authority.<br><br>The ECTN must be obtained prior to shipment and must be included on the shipping documents. The ECTN is valid for one year and must be renewed annually.', 'ECTN Central African Republic | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Central African Republic: An ECTN (Electronic Cargo Tracking Note) is a 10-digit number required for all shipments of goods from the Central African Republic (CAR) to the United States.', 'asset/maps/central-african-republic.jpg', 'An ECTN, or Export Control Certificate of Notification, is required for all shipments of controlled goods from the Central African Republic (CAR) to the United States.<br><br>The ECTN is obtained from the National Directorate of Customs and Excise (DNCE) in CAR. The shipper must apply for the ECTN at least five working days before the shipment is due to leave CAR.<br>To apply for an ECTN Ectn Central African Republic,<br>the shipper must submit the following documents to the DNCE:<br>completed ECTN application form.<br>\r\n&#x2022; copy of the commercial invoice for the shipment.<br>\r\n&#x2022; copy of the packing list for the shipment.<br>\r\n&#x2022; copy of the bill of lading for the shipment.<br><br>\r\nThe DNCE will review the documents and, if everything is in order, issue the ECTN. The ECTN must be included in the shipping documents for the shipment and presented to U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) at the time of entry into the United States. If you have any questions about the ECTN process, please contact us.', '<b>What is the ECTN and why do I need it?</b><br>The ECTN (Electronic Cargo Tracking Note) is a unique identification number assigned to each shipment of goods destined for the port of Bangui in the Central African Republic. The ECTN is required in order to track and trace shipments, as well as to ensure that the correct duties and taxes are paid on imported goods.<br><br><b>How do I obtain an Ectn Central African Republic?</b><br>Your shipping agent or the freight forwarder will apply for an ECTN on your behalf. Once the ECTN is issued, it will be valid for one year.<br><br><b>What information do I need to provide in order to obtain an ECTN Central African Republic?</b><br>In order to apply for an ECTN, you will need to provide the following information:<br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of the importer <br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of the exporter <br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of the manufacturer <br>\r\n&#x2022; A description of the goods being imported <br>\r\n&#x2022; The value of the goods being imported -The HS code of the goods being imported -The mode of transport (sea, air, land).', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(5, 'IVORY COAST', 'ivory-coast', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (3).svg', 'Ivory Coast has officially joined the list of nations using the Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) system, which gives me great pleasure. By offering a single community platform for all shipping documents, this system is intended to simplify the process of sending goods to the Ivory Coast. Shipment agents can electronically submit shipping documents using the web-based ECTN system. A distinct tracking number is then generated by the system for each shipment. Customs officials can use this number to follow the status of the shipment and check that all paperwork is in place.<br><br>The following nations presently employ the ECTN system: -Mali -Niger -Senegal -Togo -Burkina Faso -Cameroon -Congo -Gabon -Ivory Coast We advise you to use the ECTN system to speed up the transportation of merchandise to the Ivory Coast. Please check our website for additional details to better grasp ECTN.', 'ECTN Ivory | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Ivory: Ivory Coast has officially joined the list of nations using the Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) system, which gives me great pleasure.', 'asset/maps/evory-coast.jpg', 'The Ivory Coast requires all ships calling at its ports to obtain an ECTN (Electronic Cargo Tracking Note) before arrival. The ECTN is a document that ensures that the correct taxes and duties are paid on cargo imported into the Ivory Coast. It also simplifies the customs clearance process and can be obtained relatively easily.<br><br><b>Here is a step-by-step guide on how to obtain an ECTN for your shipment to the Ivory Coast:</b><br>1. Collect the necessary documents To apply for an ECTN, you will need the following documents: -<br>\r\n&#x2022; Signed ECTN application form  <br>\r\n&#x2022; Copy of the bill of lading or air waybill    <br>\r\n&#x2022; Commercial invoice    <br>\r\n&#x2022; Packing list    <br>\r\n2. Apply Once you have gathered all of the required documents, you can submit the application to the National Agency for the Promotion of Investment and Export (ANAPI). ANAPI is responsible for issuing ECTNs in the Ivory Coast. The application can be submitted online, by mail, or in person at the ANAPI office in Abidjan.', '<b>What is the purpose of the ECTN?</b><br>The ECTN is used to track shipments of cargo leaving the European Union. The ECTN ensures that the proper export licenses and taxes are paid.<br><br><b>What information is required to obtain an ECTN? \r\nTo obtain an ECTN, the following information is required:</b><br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of the shipper <br>\r\n&#x2022; name and address of the consignee <br>\r\n&#x2022; port of loading <br>\r\n&#x2022; port of discharge <br>\r\n&#x2022; country of destination <br>\r\n&#x2022; Harmonized System code for the cargo <br>\r\n&#x2022; value of the cargo <br>\r\n&#x2022; weight of the cargo <br>\r\n&#x2022; volume of the cargo.<br><br>\r\n<b>How is the ECTN obtained?</b><br>\r\nThe ECTN is obtained by applying for an export license with the local Chamber of Commerce.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(6, 'EQUATORIAL GUINEA', 'equatorial-guinea', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (1).svg', 'All ports in Equatorial Guinea will need an ECTN (Electronic Cargo Tracking Note) starting on January 1st, 2021, for all imports and exports. Prior to shipment, this essential document must be secured; otherwise, there may be delays and perhaps even fines. Obtaining an ECTN is an easy and simple process. On behalf of their clients, shipping firms or their representatives should apply for the document, and the ECTN will be provided within 24 hours. The only details needed are the names and addresses of the shipper, the consignee, and the Bill of Lading (B/L) number. The B/L number must remain the same for many shipments in order for the ECTN to be utilised. The ECTN is valid for one year. A new ECTN must be obtained if the B/L number changes. The ECTN is free, and there is no need to renew it every year. The government of Equatorial Guinea has implemented a number of new maritime regulations, including the ECTN.', 'ECTN Equatorial Guinea | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Equatorial Guinea: For all cargo going to Equatorial Guinea, an ECTN loading document is required. Obtaining an ECTN is required if you are sending products to Equatorial Guinea (Export Control and Tracking Number).', 'asset/maps/equatorial-geunia.jpg', 'Ships must have the ECTN (Equatorial Guinea Certificate of Navigation) in order to navigate the territorial waters of Equatorial Guinea. The Directorate General of Merchant Marine (DGMM) issues certificates that are valid for a year. The following documents must be supplied in order to receive the certificate: - Retailer registry - A seaworthiness certificate, an insurance certificate, a roster of the crew, the captain\'s passport, and evidence that the registration price has been paid. All vessels, including those used for fishing, that enters Equatorial Guinean seas must have an ECTN.<br><br>These actions must be taken in order to receive an ECTN in Equatorial Guinea:<br>1. A current passport is a need.<br>2. A current visa is required.<br>3. A letter of invitation from a business or person in Equatorial Guinea is required.<br>4. A return ticket is required.<br>5. You must have a confirmation letter from the host institution or proof of hotel arrangements.<br> 6. You must demonstrate that you have the resources to sustain your stay in Equatorial Guinea.<br>7. Immunization records are required.<br>8. At least 15 days before your arrival in Equatorial Guinea, you must submit your application to the Directorate General of Consular Affairs.<br>9. You have to pay the required fees.', '<b>What details must I provide in my application for an ECTN?</b><br>\r\nYou must supply the following details in order to apply for an ECTN:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Your name <br>\r\n&#x2022; The name of your business <br>\r\n&#x2022; Your contact details <br>\r\n&#x2022; A description of the shipment\'s contents <br>\r\n&#x2022; The item\'s Harmonized System (HS) code <br> <br>\r\n<b>An ECTN is valid for how long?</b><br>The validity of an ECTN is one year from the date of issuance.<br><br><b>How can I submit an ECTN application?</b><br>Through an online application platform run by the Ministry of Industry, Trade, and Investment, ECTN applications can be submitted.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', 'A freight forwarder will normally get the ECTN on your behalf if you hire them to export your products. However, it\'s crucial to confirm with your freight forwarder that they will do this for you. If your forwarder does not provide this service, you could be compelled to get the ECTN yourself. Through Equatorial Guinea\'s Ministry of Finance, you can submit an application for an ECTN. You may learn more on their website, and the application procedure is quite simple. You must provide your freight forwarder with your ECTN once you get it so they may include it in your shipment papers. This will guarantee that your goods can pass through customs quickly.'),
(7, 'CAMEROON', 'cameroon', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (5).svg', 'The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a document which is now mandatory for all shipments of cargo departing from the port of Douala, Cameroon. The ECTN replaces the paper-based Bill of Lading and is a requirement of the International Maritime Organization (IMO).<br><br>The ECTN is an initiative of the Cameroonian port authorities and the IMO to improve security and efficiency in the shipping industry. The ECTN allows for real-time tracking of cargo shipments and provides a tamper-proof record of the shipment. The ECTN is also intended to streamline the customs clearance process and reduce the risk of fraudulent shipments.<br><br>The ECTN system was piloted in the port of Douala in 2016 and is now mandatory for all cargo departing from Cameroon. All shipping lines operating in the port of Douala are required to participate in the ECTN system.<br><br>The ECTN is a positive step forward for the shipping industry in Cameroon. The real-time tracking of shipments will improve security and efficiency, and the tamper-proof record will help to reduce the risk of fraud.', 'ECTN Cameroon | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Cameroon: The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a document which is now mandatory for all shipments of cargo departing from the port of Douala, Cameroon. ', 'asset/maps/camaroon.jpg', 'ECTN of CAMEROON The ECTN is a document required for the shipment of certain types of goods to Cameroon.<br>The ECTN is obtained from the National Agency for the Promotion of Investments (ANAPI), which is the competent authority in Cameroon. <br><br><b>To obtain an ECTN, the following documents must be submitted to ANAPI:</b><br>\r\n&#x2022; a completed and signed ECTN application form  <br>\r\n&#x2022; a commercial invoice  <br>\r\n&#x2022; a packing list  <br>\r\n&#x2022; a bill of lading (or air waybill) ANAPI may request additional documents as needed. <br><br>\r\nOnce the ECTN is issued, it must be presented to the shipping company in order to have the goods shipped. The ECTN is valid for one year from the date of issue.', '<b>How is Cameroon Ectn obtained? </b><br><br>An ECTN can be obtained by the registered consignor or their authorized representative prior to shipment.<br><br><b>Why is an Cameroon Ectn required?</b><br><br>An <b>Cameroon Ectn</b> is required in order to facilitate the electronic tracking of shipments of cargo and to ensure that the proper customs duties and taxes are paid.<br><br><b>What information is required to obtain an ECTN?</b><br>In order to obtain an Cameroon Ectn, the following information is required:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Identity of the registered consignor  <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and address of the shipper  <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and address of the consignee <br>\r\n&#x2022; Port of loading <br>\r\n&#x2022; Port of discharge <br>\r\n&#x2022; Description of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Value of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Weight of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Volume of the goods. <br>', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(8, 'BURUNDI', 'burundi', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (6).svg', 'According to the latest information, the ECTN of BURUNDI is now available. This system is designed to streamline the process of customs clearance and reduce the cost of doing business in the country.<br><br>The ECTN of BURUNDI is a computerized system that will allow businesses to submit their customs declarations electronically. This will save time and money, as well as improve the efficiency of the customs clearance process.<br><br>The ECTN of BURUNDI is mandatory for all imports and exports of goods into and out of the country. businesses that fail to comply with this requirement will be subject to penalties. If you are doing business in BURUNDI, it is important to be aware of this new requirement and to make sure that you comply.<br><br>For more information, please contact your local customs office.', 'ECTN Burundi | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Burundi: ECTN of BURUNDI According to the latest information, the ECTN of BURUNDI is now available. Contact us Now.', 'asset/maps/burundi.jpg', 'BURUNDI has introduced a new regulation for shipments requiring an Export Control Transport Document (ECTN). The ECTN is now mandatory for all shipments of cargo to BURUNDI regardless of the value and must be obtained before Cargo Release. The ECTN is an electronic document which is submitted to the shipping line or freight forwarder, who will include the number on the Bill of Lading. The ECTN must be obtained from the National Office for Transport Control (ONCT) in BURUNDI.<br><br>The completed application form, along with the required documents, must be submitted to the ONCT. <br><b>The following documents are required:</b><br>\r\n&#x2022; The Bill of Lading or Air Waybill  <br>\r\n&#x2022; A letter of Credit -A packing list  <br>\r\n&#x2022; A commercial invoice <br>\r\n&#x2022; A certificate of origin (if required) <br>\r\n&#x2022; The ECTN application form The ECTN application form must be completed in full and signed by the applicant. The completed form and required documents can be submitted by email, fax, or in person at the ONCT.', '<b>Why was the ECTN system introduced?</b><br>The ECTN system was introduced in order to streamline the export process and to make it easier and faster for businesses to export from the Republic of Burundi.<br><br><b>How do I get an ECTN for Burundi?</b><br>All you need to do is to contact your freight forwarder or shipping agent and they will help you to obtain an ECTN.<br><br><b>What are the benefits of using the ECTN system?</b><br>The main benefits of using the ECTN system are • It is faster and easier to obtain an ECTN than a paper-based CTN.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(9, 'THE DEMOCRATIC\r\nREPUBLIC OF CONGO', 'the-democratic-republic-of-congo', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (4).svg', 'The ECTN system is used in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) to control the export of goods from the country. The ECTN is a document that is required for all exports from the DRC and must be obtained from the Chambers of Commerce in the country of origin. <br>The ECTN must be presented to the customs authorities in the DRC at the time of export, and the exporting company must have a valid ECTN for the goods being exported. The ECTN system was introduced in the DRC in 2008 and is administered by the Ministry of Industry and Mines. The ECTN is valid for one year from the date of issuance and must be renewed annually.', 'ECTN The Democratic Republic Of Congo | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN The Democratic Republic Of Congo: The ECTN system is used in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) to control the export of goods from the country.', 'asset/maps/congo-the-democratic-republic.jpg', 'An ECTN, or Export Control Certificate Number, is required for all shipments of goods from the DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF THE CONGO. The ECTN is obtained from the National Agency for the Control of Exports (ANEM in French), and the shipping company will need<br>The following documentation in order to apply for the certificate:<br>1. A commercial invoice for the goods being shipped<br>2. A packing list for the goods being shipped <br>3. A letter of credit or another payment guarantee<br>4. A certificate of origin for the goods being shipped<br>5. A license from ANEM if the goods being shipped fall under the category of \"strategic goods\"<br>6. An insurance policy for the goods being shipped The shipping company will then submit the above documentation to ANEM, along with the ECTN application form.<br><br>Once the ECTN has been issued, it must be placed on the bill of lading for the shipment. If you have any questions about obtaining an ECTN for your shipment from the DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF THE CONGO, please contact us. We are happy to help!', '<b>What types of goods require an Ectn Democratic Republic Of the Congo?</b><br>The following types of goods require an ECTN to be exported from the Democratic Republic of the Congo: -Strategic goods -Mineral ores - timber - Firearms.<br><br><b>How do I obtain an Ectn Democratic Republic Of the Congo?</b><br>An ECTN can be obtained from the Export Control and Transport Authority of the Democratic Republic of the Congo.<br><br><b>How much does an ECTN cost?</b><br>The fee for an ECTN is $250.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(10, 'CHAD', 'chad', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (10).svg', 'All marine goods arriving in Chad must be covered by a Cargo Tracking Note (CTN) or Electronic Cargo Tracking Note, according to a rule set out by the Chad Shippers Council (ECTN). This requirement is in addition to the current one that states that a bill of lading must be attached to every piece of cargo.<br><br>From loading at the port of origin through arrival at the destination, the cargo is tracked via a document known as the CTN or ECTN. To clear the goods for importation, Customs must receive the paperwork, which was provided by the shipping business, at the port of destination. To clear the goods for importation, the CTN or ECTN must be obtained before shipping and shown to Customs at the port of destination.', 'ECTN Chad | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Chad: All marine goods arriving in Chad must be covered by a Cargo Tracking Note (CTN) or Electronic Cargo Tracking Note, according to a rule set out by the Chad Shippers Council (ECTN). ', 'asset/maps/chad.jpg', 'All marine goods arriving in Chad must be covered by a Cargo Tracking Note (CTN) or Electronic Cargo Tracking Note, according to a statement from the Chad Shippers Council (ECTN). On January 1st, 2020, this new requirement will go into force. Every shipping company doing business in Chad needs to make sure that all of its boats abide by the new law.<br><br>The CTN is a record that keeps track of a shipment\'s journey from its origin to its final destination. It must be obtained in advance of shipping from the Chad Shippers Council and is necessary for all goods entering Chad. The ECTN, which is the CTN\'s electronic counterpart, may be downloaded on the Council\'s website. Before their goods reach Chad, all shipping companies must confirm they have the appropriate papers.', '<b>Why is there a change now?</b><br><br>The reason for this modification is that the Chadian government mandates that all shipments have an ECTN.<br><br><b>What must I do to obtain an ECTN?</b><br><br>You need to get an ECTN from the National Chamber of Commerce in Chad if you\'re shipping to that country.<br><br><b>What is the price of an ECTN?</b><br><br>The value of the package determines how much an ECTN will cost. The ECTN will cost 5,000 CFA francs for shipments valued at less than 5,000,000 CFA francs. The ECTN will cost 10,000 CFA francs for shipments valued at more than 5,000,000 CFA francs.<br><br><b>What is an ECTN used for?</b><br><br>To follow shipments and make sure all export documentation is in order, utilise an ECTN. Calculating the tariffs and taxes due on shipments is another application for it.<br><br><b>How can I get an ECTN?</b><br><br>You may get ECTNs from the shipping company. You will have to supply the following details: -The name and address of your consignee -The port of destination -The anticipated arrival date -A list of the things being transported.<br><br><b>What advantages come with employing an ECTN?</b><br><br>Reduced paperwork, quicker shipment processing, improved accuracy in calculating customs and taxes due, and increased security of shipments are just a few advantages that ECTNs provide.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', 'All marine goods arriving in Chad must be covered by a Cargo Tracking Note (CTN) or Electronic Cargo Tracking Note, according to a statement from the Chad Shippers Council (ECTN).<br><br>All importers and shipping businesses who may be impacted by this change are thus given formal notice. A document called the CTN makes it possible to trace shipments of marine commodities. It is issued by the shipping firm and has to be filed with the customs office in the destination nation before the goods arrive. Since it is more effective and straightforward to track than the paper form, the ECTN, an electronic counterpart of the CTN, is becoming more and more popular.<br><br>All cargo arriving in Chad after the change takes effect on January 1st, 2020, must have a CTN or ECTN. The goods will be refused and sent back to the sender if this criterion is not met. It is crucial to make sure you are knowledgeable about the CTN or ECTN regulations and that you have the proper paperwork in place if you are an importer or shipping firm that will be impacted by this change.'),
(11, 'ANGOLA', 'angola', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (9).svg', 'The issuance of an ECTN is now mandatory for all FCL shipments to or from the port of Luanda, Angola. This regulation was put in place to streamline the loading and unloading of containers at the port, and to help prevent delays. An ECTN is a 10-digit number that must be obtained prior to shipping.<br><br>It can be obtained from the shipping company or the importer/exporter. If you are shipping to or from Angola, be sure to obtain an ECTN before your shipment departs. This will help ensure a smooth and efficient process at the port.', 'ECTN Angola | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Angola: The issuance of an ECTN is now mandatory for all FCL shipments to or from the port of Luanda, Angola. Contact us now.', 'asset/maps/angola.jpg', 'The procedure for getting an ECTN of ANGOLA getting an ECTN (Export Control Threat Number) for ANGOLA is not as complicated as it might seem at first. In this article, we will guide you through the entire process so that you can obtain your ECTN with ease. The first step is to contact the Export Control Officer (ECO) at the ANGOLA Embassy.<br><br>The ECO will then provide you with the necessary paperwork, which you will need to fill out and return. Next, you will need to obtain a certificate of origin from the Chamber of Commerce. This document will need to be notarized. Once you have obtained the certificate of origin, you will need to submit it, along with the rest of the required paperwork, to the ECO.<br><br>The ECO will then issue you an ECTN. It is important to note that the ECTN is valid for one year and must be renewed annually. Also, keep in mind that the ECTN is not required for every shipment; only those that meet the criteria specified by the ANGOLA government.', '<b>What information is required to obtain an ECTN?</b><br><br>In order to obtain an ECTN, the following information is required: - Shipper information - Consignee information - Notifier information - Bill of lading or air waybill number - Description of goods - HS code of goods - Net weight of goods - Value of goods <br><br><b>How long does it take to obtain an ECTN?</b><br><br>The ECTN application must be submitted online at least 5 days prior to shipment. Once the application has been submitted, it can take up to 3 days to receive the ECTN. How much does an ECTN cost? An ECTN costs $50 USD and must be paid prior to shipment.<br><br><b>Is an ECTN required for every shipment to Angola?</b><br><br>Yes, an ECTN is required for every shipment of controlled goods to Angola.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(12, 'MALI', 'mali', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (12).svg', 'Mali is a landlocked country in West Africa. Mali is bordered by Algeria to the north, Niger to the east, Burkina Faso to the south, Guinea to the southwest, Senegal to the west, and Mauritania to the northwest. Its population is estimated to be 18 million. Its capital is Bamako. Mali is a poor country with underdeveloped infrastructure. The vast majority of the population is engaged in subsistence agriculture. About one-third of the population is nomadic or semi-nomadic. Manganese, gold, and phosphate deposits are Mali\'s main natural resources. Mali is a member of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS).<br><br>ECOWAS is a regional economic union of fifteen countries located in West Africa. The primary purpose of ECOWAS is to promote economic integration and cooperation among its member states. The Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) has a Certificate of Origin regime known as the ECOWAS Trade Liberalization Scheme (ETLS). The ETLS allows for the free movement of goods between member states.', 'ECTN Mali | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Mali: Mali is a landlocked country in West Africa. Mali is bordered by Algeria to the north, Niger to the east, Burkina Faso to the south, Guinea to the southwest, Senegal to the west, and Mauritania to the northwest. ', 'asset/maps/mali.jpg', 'Procedure for getting an ECTN of MALI An ECTN, or Export Control Text Note, is required for the export of certain goods from Mali. The ECTN is obtained from the Ministry of Trade and Industry in Bamako, Mali. To obtain an ECTN,<br><br>\r\n<b>The following documents must be submitted to the Ministry:</b> <br>1. A letter of request from the exporter<br>2. A commercial invoice<br>3. A packing list<br>4. A bill of lading<br>The Ministry will issue the ECTN once the above documents have been submitted and reviewed. The ECTN must then be presented to the customs authority at the port of export in order to obtain permission to export the goods.', '<b>How do I obtain an ECTN Mali?</b><br>To obtain an ECTN, you must submit a completed export control license application to BIS. You can find the export control license application on the BIS website.<br><br><b>How long is an ECTN Mali valid?</b><br>An ECTN is valid for one year from the date of issuance.<br><br><b>Do I need an ECTN if I am exporting from the United States to Mali?</b><br>Yes, you will need an ECTN if you are exporting from the United States to Mali.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(13, 'NIGER', 'niger', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (13).svg', 'The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a mandatory document for all shipments of cargo destined for Niger. The ECTN must be obtained prior to shipment and must be presented to Nigerian Customs upon arrival of the cargo in Niger. The ECTN is obtained from the Nigerian Shippers\' Council (NSC) and is valid for a period of six months from the date of issue. The ECTN must be renewed every six months in order to maintain its validity. The ECTN is used by Nigerian Customs to track and trace cargo shipments and to assess duties and taxes due on imported goods. The ECTN is also used to monitor and control the importation of prohibited and restricted goods into Niger. The ECTN system was introduced in Nigeria in 2009 in order to streamline the import and export procedures and to reduce the time and cost associated with shipping cargo to and from Nigeria.', 'ECTN Niger | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Niger: The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a mandatory document for all shipments of cargo destined for Niger. Contact us Now.', 'asset/maps/niger.jpg', 'An ECTN, or Export Control Tracking Number, is required for all shipments of products subject to export control regulations from Niger.,, Exporters must apply for an ECTN at least 5 working days prior to shipment.,,The ECTN must be applied for through the online application system.,,Shipments of products subject to export control regulations without a valid ECTN will be subject to delays and may be refused.,,To apply for an ECTN, exporters will need the following information:<br><br>- A copy of the commercial invoice  <br>- A copy of the bill of lading or air waybill <br>- A list of the products being shipped, including HS codes and product descriptions <br>- The importer\'s name and address <br>- The destination country <br>- The reason for the export (e.g. for repairs, for exhibition, for personal use, etc).<br><br>,, Once the ECTN has been applied for, the exporter will receive a confirmation email with a tracking number.,,This tracking number must be included on the shipping documents and must be presented to customs upon arrival of the shipment.', '<b>How much does an ECTN cost?</b><br><br>The price of an ECTN is based on the package\'s worth. For shipments worth less than 5,000,000 CFA francs, the ECTN will cost you 5,000 CFA francs. For shipments priced at more than 5,000,000 CFA francs, the ECTN will cost 10,000 CFA francs.<br><br><b>What is the purpose of an ECTN to Niger?</b><br><br>Use an ECTN to track shipments and verify that all export documentation is valid. Another use for it is to figure out the taxes and tariffs owed on shipments.<br><br><b>How do I acquire an ECTN?</b><br><br> ECTNs could be available from the shipping firm. You must provide the following information:<br>-The consignee\'s name and address <br> -The port of destination <br>-The scheduled arrival date.', 'Document required for ECTN of NIGER An ECTN, or Export Control Tracking Number, is required for the export of certain goods from Niger.,,The ECTN is obtained from the Nigerien authorities prior to export and must be presented to the shipping company at the time of export.,,The ECTN is valid for a period of one year and must be renewed annually.,,Exporters should contact the Nigerien authorities well in advance of their planned exports in order to obtain the necessary ECTN.', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(14, 'SIERRA LEONE', 'sierra-leone', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (14).svg', 'Sierra Leone is a beautiful country located in West Africa. The people of Sierra Leone are very friendly and hospitable. The country is rich in natural resources, such as diamonds, gold, and iron ore. The Sierra Leonean economy is growing and the country is making great strides in its development. The government of Sierra Leone is committed to improving the lives of its people and attracting foreign investment.<br><br>The Sierra Leone Investment and Export Promotion Agency (SLIEPA) is the primary agency responsible for promoting investment and exports in Sierra Leone. SLIEPA is committed to creating a conducive environment for investments and exports, and offers a range of services to investors and exporters.<br><br>The Sierra Leone Chamber of Commerce and Industry (SLCCI) is the leading private sector organization in Sierra Leone. The SLCCI promotes and protects the interests of businesses in Sierra Leone. The ECTN is a document that is required for all shipments of goods from Sierra Leone. The ECTN must be obtained from the Sierra Leonean Embassy or Consulate before goods can be shipped. The ECTN is valid for one year from the date of issuance.', 'ECTN Sierra Leone | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Sierra Leone: The ECTN must be obtained from the Sierra Leonean Embassy or Consulate before goods can be shipped. ', 'asset/maps/sierra-leone.jpg', 'The Export Control act is the legal framework that governs the export of strategic goods and technology from Sierra Leone. The act is administered by the Directorate of Trade and Investment, under the Ministry of Trade and Industry. To export controlled goods or technology from Sierra Leone, you must first obtain an export permit from the Directorate of Trade and Investment. The permit application must be accompanied by a completed consignment information form, which must be certified by the Customs and Excise Department. Once the permit has been issued, the goods must be presented to the Customs and Excise Department for clearance. The Customs Declaration must be accompanied by the export permit, and the goods must be declared to Customs in the prescribed manner.<br><br><b>The export of controlled goods or technology from Sierra Leone is subject to a number of restrictions and controls. These include</b><br>\r\n&#x2022; A requirement that the goods are for the exclusive use of the Sierra Leonean government or a specified person or institution, <br>\r\n&#x2022; A requirement that the goods are intended for re-export, <br>\r\n&#x2022; A requirement that the goods are not to be trans-shipped, <br>\r\n&#x2022; A requirement that the goods are not to be sold or disposed of in Sierra Leone without the prior approval. <br>', '<b>How did the ECTN system come about?</b><br>The ECTN system was put in place to speed up and simplify the export procedure for companies doing business in the Republic of Burundi.<br><br><b>How can I acquire an Ectn Sierra Leone?</b><br>To get an Ectn Sierra Leone, all you have to do is get in touch with your freight forwarder or shipping agent.<br><br><b>What advantages does using the ECTN system offer?</b><br>The key advantages of adopting the ECTN system are:<br>\r\n• Getting an ECTN is quicker and simpler than getting a paper-based CTN.', 'Bill of Lading.,,Commercial Invoice.,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice).,,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(15, 'SENEGAL', 'senegal', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (15).svg', 'The ECTN is a document which is required for all shipments of cargo to Senegal. It is obtained from the shipping company and must be presented to Senegalese customs upon arrival of the shipment.<br><br>The ECTN is valid for one year and can be used for multiple shipments. It is important to note that the ECTN is not required for shipments of personal effects. If you are shipping cargo to Senegal, you will need to obtain an ECTN (E-Certificate of Territorial Coverage).<br><br>The ECTN is a document which is required by Senegalese customs and must be presented at the time of arrival of your shipment. The ECTN is obtained from the shipping company and is valid for one year. It can be used for multiple shipments and is an important document to have when shipping cargo to Senegal.', 'ECTN Senegal | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Senegal: ECTN is a mandatory loading document for all shipments to Senegal. Contact us Now.', 'asset/maps/senegal.jpg', 'In order to get an ECTN (Export Control Trading Number) from Senegal, you must first have a company registered in Senegal. Once you have a company registered, you can then apply for an ECTN through the Senegalese Chamber of Commerce.<br><br><b>The following is a list of the required documents needed in order to apply for an Ectn Senegal:</b><br>\r\n&#x2022; A completed and signed ECTN application form <br>\r\n&#x2022; A letter from the company stating that the applicant is authorised to apply for an ECTN on behalf of the company <br>\r\n&#x2022; An invoice or contract for the export of the goods Once you have gathered all of the required documents, you can submit them to the Senegalese Chamber of Commerce along with the application fee. It can take up to 21 days to receive an ECTN from Senegal.', '<b>How can I acquire an Ectn Senegal?</b><br>Typically, your shipping business will handle securing an ECTN on your behalf. You can apply for an ECTN on the website of the Directorate-General for Taxation and Customs Union of the European Union if you are organising your own shipment.<br><br><b>What details must I give in order to receive an Ectn Senegal?</b><br>You must supply the following details in order to apply for an ECTN:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Your name and contact information <br>\r\n&#x2022; The shipper\'s name and contact details  <br>\r\n&#x2022; The consignee\'s name and contact details <br>\r\n&#x2022; The ports for loading and unloading <br>\r\n&#x2022; The anticipated time of departure -The anticipated time of arrival -The kind of goods being sent', 'Bill of Lading.,,Commercial Invoice.,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice).,,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL);
