(16, 'SOUTH SUDAN', 'south-sudan', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (16).svg', 'The Export Control Trade Network (ECTN) of South Sudan is a tool that was established by the Government of South Sudan to help streamline the process of exporting goods from South Sudan.<br><br>The ECTN is a web-based portal that provides a single window for exporters to register their goods and obtain the necessary export permits and licenses. The ECTN also provides a platform for government agencies to share information and work together to streamline the export process. The ECTN was established in response to the many challenges that exporters face in exporting goods from South Sudan.', 'ECTN South Sudan | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN South Sudan: The Export Control Trade Network (ECTN) of South Sudan is a tool that was established by the Government of South Sudan to help streamline the process of exporting goods from South Sudan.', 'asset/maps/south-sudan.jpg', 'To obtain an ECCN of South Sudan, the following documents must be submitted to the South Sudanese Ministry of Commerce and Industry:<br>1. A completed ECCN of South Sudan application form.<br>2. A letter from the company requesting the ECCN of South Sudan, addressed to the South Sudanese Ministry of Commerce and Industry.<br>3. A letter from the company\'s Chamber of Commerce, confirming the company\'s membership.<br>4. A copy of the company\'s commercial registration certificate.<br>5. A copy of the company\'s VAT registration certificate.<br>6. A copy of the company\'s import/export license.<br>7. A copy of the invoice for the controlled goods to be imported into South Sudan.<br>8. A copy of the packing list for the controlled goods.', '<b>How does an ECTN work?</b><br><br>The ECTN is assigned to a shipment by the carrier at the point of origin. The ECTN travels with the shipment and is updated at each major milestone, such as when the shipment is loaded onto the vessel, arrives at the port of destination, and is discharged from the vessel. The ECTN can also be used to track the status of the shipment in transit, such as if it has been delayed or is running behind schedule.<br><br><b>Why is an ECTN required for shipments to South Sudan?</b><br><br>The ECTN is required for all shipments of cargo travelling to South Sudan by sea. This is due to the fact that South Sudan is a landlocked country, meaning that all shipments of cargo must travel through neighbouring countries before reaching their final destination. The ECTN allows for the efficient tracking and tracing of these shipments. ', 'Bill of Lading.,,Commercial Invoice.,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice).,,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(17, 'TOGO', 'togo', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (17).svg', 'The ECTN is a document that is required for all shipments of goods from the Republic of Togo destined for the European Union (EU). The ECTN replaces the requirement for an export license for all shipments to the EU from Togo and is used by Customs in the EU to control the import of goods from Togo.<br><br>The ECTN must be obtained from the Togolese customs authority, ANE, prior to shipment and must be presented to the shipping company when the goods are exported from Togo.<br><br>The ECTN is valid for one year from the date of issue and can be used for multiple shipments of goods during that period. If you are exporting goods from Togo to the EU, you will need to obtain an ECTN prior to shipment.', 'ECTN Togo | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Togo: The ECTN must be obtained from the Togolese customs authority, ANE, prior to shipment and must be presented to the shipping company when the goods are exported from Togo.', 'asset/maps/togo.jpg', 'According to the Official website of the Togolese Republic, an exporter must request an ECTN (Electronic Cargo Tracking Note) from the Chamber of Commerce before shipping their goods. The ECTN is obtained from the Port Authorities.<br><br>The ECTN is an identification number that is tracking the movement of the shipment from the port of loading to the port of destination. This information is used by the customs authorities to streamline the customs clearance process.<br><br>The ECTN must be obtained prior to shipment and must be included on the Bill of Lading. If you are shipping goods to Togo, you will need to obtain an ECTN prior to shipment. You can obtain the ECTN from the Togolese Chamber of Commerce or from the Port Authorities.', '<b></b>How do I get an Ectn Togo? </b><br><br>The Ectn Togocan be obtained from the Togolese National Shippers’ Council (NSC) or any licensed freight forwarder. Freight forwarders can apply for the ECTN on behalf of their clients.<br><br><b>What information do I need to apply for an ECTN Togo? </b><br><br>\r\nTo apply for an ECTN, you will need the following information:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and address of the shipper <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and address of the consignee <br>\r\n&#x2022; Ports of loading and discharge <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name of the vessel <br>\r\n&#x2022; Estimated time of arrival <br>\r\n&#x2022; Bill of lading or air waybill number -The dimensions and weight of the cargo <br>\r\n&#x2022; Commodity description <br>\r\n&#x2022; Value of the cargo\r\n\r\n', 'Bill of Lading.,,Commercial Invoice.,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice).,,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(18, 'GABON', 'gabon', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (18).svg', 'ECTN OF GABON The ECTN is an administrative document obligatory for the shipments of merchandise departing from the territory of a country member of the ECTN system and bound for another country member of the same system.<br><br>The ECTN must be obtained by the consignor before shipment and must be transmitted to the carrier who will present it to the customs authorities of the country of destination. The ECTN is a single document for all Member States of the Central African Economic and Monetary Community (CEMAC). This document is also called a \"single administrative document\" or \"single window\".<br><br>The ECTN replaces the \"carnet de passage en douane\" (CPD) which was used previously for shipments between CEMAC countries.', 'ECTN Gabon | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Gabon: ECTN OF GABON The ECTN is an administrative document obligatory for the shipments of merchandise departing from the territory of a country member of the ECTN system and bound for another country member of the same system.', 'asset/maps/gabon.jpg', 'Assuming you would like a blog titled \"ECTN of GABON\": The ECTN, or Export Control and Tracking Number, is mandatory for all shipments of goods from the Republic of Gabon bound for the European Union (EU).<br><br>The ECTN is obtained from the National Agency for Export Control (ANADIE) and must be obtained prior to shipping. The ECTN must be obtained for each individual shipment, and must be included on the shipping documents. The ECTN is valid for 10 days from the date of issuance.<br><b>The ECTN procedure is as follows:</b><br>1. The exporter must have an ANADIE registration number.<br>2. The exporter must complete the ECTN application form, which is available on the ANADIE  website.<br>3. The completed application form, along with the required supporting documents, must be  submitted to ANADIE.<br>4. ANADIE will review the application and, if everything is in order, will issue the ECTN.<br>5. The ECTN must then be included on the shipping documents.', '<b>How do I get an ECTN GABON?</b><br><br>You can apply for an ECTN through the Chamber of Commerce website. The application process is simple and takes only a few minutes to complete.', 'Bill of Lading.,,Commercial Invoice.,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice).,,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(19, 'GUINEA', 'guinea', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (19).svg', 'The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a document required for the import and export of cargo in the Republic of Guinea. The ECTN is obtained from the National Office of Transport and Transit (ONTT) and is valid for a period of 30 days. The ECTN must be presented at the port of entry/exit in Guinea and must be accompanied by a Bill of Lading or Air Waybill. <br><br>The ECTN is valid for a single shipment and must be registered in the name of the consignee. The ECTN can be obtained from the ONTT website or from the office of the consignee in Guinea. The ECTN must be obtained prior to the shipment of goods to Guinea and must be presented at the port of entry/exit.', 'ECTN Guinea | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Guinea: The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a document required for the import and export of cargo in the Republic of Guinea. Contact us now.', 'asset/maps/guinea.jpg', 'The Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN) is a document that is required for all shipments of cargo to the Republic of Guinea. The ECTN is obtained from the Guinea National Carrier, Societe Nationale des Transports Africains (SONATRAC). This document is required in order to track the shipment and to ensure that the cargo arrives at its destination safely. The ECTN is valid for one year and must be renewed annually. There is no fee for the ECTN, but there is a minimum shipment value of $5,000 USD that must be met in order for the ECTN to be issued.<br><b>The ECTN can be obtained by following these steps:</b><br>1) Apply for an ECTN through SONATRAC<br>2) Fill out the application form and submit it to SONATRAC<br>3) SONATRAC will review the application and issue the ECTN<br>4) The ECTN will be valid for one year from the date of issue.', '<b>What is an Ectn Guinea?</b><br><br>An ECTN is an Export Control Document Number issued by the customs authorities of the exporting country. It is required for all shipments of controlled goods from Guinea.\r\n<br><br><b>Who needs an Ectn Guinea?</b><br><br>All businesses that export controlled goods from Guinea must have an ECTN.<br><br><b>How do I apply for an Ectn Guinea?</b><br><br>You can apply for an ECTN online or at the nearest Guinea customs office.<br><br><b>How much does an Ectn Guinea cost?</b><br><br>The cost of an ECTN depends on the value of the goods being exported.<br><br><b>What information do I need to provide to apply for an Ectn Guinea?</b><br><br>When applying for an ECTN, you will need to provide the following information: - A description of the goods being exported - The value of the goods - The Harmonized System (HS) code for the goods - The name and address of the consignee - The name and address of the importer - The country of destination.', 'Bill of Lading.,,Commercial Invoice.,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice).,,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(20, 'MADAGASCAR', 'madagascar', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (23).svg', 'Madagascar is an island country off the southeastern coast of Africa in the Indian Ocean. The island is approximately the size of Texas and is the fourth largest island in the world. Madagascar is home to a variety of unique plants and animals, many of which are found nowhere else on earth. The country is also one of the poorest in the world, with high levels of poverty and disease.<br><br>Madagascar is a member of the United Nations, the African Union, and the Southern African Development Community. Madagascar is also a signatory to the Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court. The country is divided into six provinces: Antananarivo, Fianarantsoa, Mahajanga, Toamasina, Toliara, and Antsiranana. The capital and largest city is Antananarivo, with a population of over 2.8 million. Other major cities include Toamasina, Mahajanga, Fianarantsoa, Antsiranana, and Toliara. Madagascar has a tropical climate, with a wet season from November to April and a dry season from May to October. The average annual temperature is 23 degrees Celsius (73 degrees Fahrenheit).', 'ECTN Madagascar | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Madagascar: ECTN is a mandatory loading document for all shipments to Madagascar. Contact us Now.', 'asset/maps/madagascar.jpg', ' In the past two decades, however, these trends have been reversed, and Madagascar has been emerging as a stable democracy with a growing economy. A key part of Madagascar\'s economic success has been its willingness to open up its economy to foreign trade and investment. One way that the country has encouraged foreign trade is by issuing an Electronic Consignment Note (ECTN) for all shipments of goods bound for Madagascar.<br><br>An ECTN is an electronic document that serves as a certificate of origin and a shipping manifest for goods being exported. The ECTN is issued by the Madagascar Chamber of Commerce and is required for all exports from Madagascar. The ECTN process is relatively simple and straightforward. First, the exporter must obtain a certificate of origin from the Chamber of Commerce.', 'If you are planning on travelling to Madagascar, you will need to obtain an Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN).<br><br>Here are some frequently asked questions about ECTNs to help make the process as smooth as possible.<br><br><b>What is an ECTN?</b><br>An Electronic Cargo Tracking Note is an electronic document that is required for all shipments of goods to Madagascar. The ECTN is used to track and trace shipments, as well as to provide customs clearance information.<br><br><b>Who needs an Ectn Madagascar?</b><br>All shippers of goods to Madagascar are required to obtain an ECTN.<br><br><b>How do I get an Ectn Madagascar?</b><br>ECTN can be obtained through the Madagascar Customs website.<br><br><b>What information do I need to provide to get an Ectn Madagascar ?</b><br>In order to obtain an ECTN, you will need to provide the following information:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and contact information of the shipper <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and contact information of the consignee -The names and contact information of the carriers <br>\r\n&#x2022; The port of loading -The port of discharge <br>\r\n&#x2022; Description of the goods being shipped <br>\r\n&#x2022; Value of the goods', 'An ECTN, or Export Control Documentation Number, is required for all shipments of cargo leaving Madagascar.<br><br>This document ensures that your cargo will be cleared through customs quickly and without any delays.<br><br>To obtain an ECTN, you will need to provide the following information to your freight forwarder:<br>-A list of the items you are exporting<br>-The value of the shipment<br>-The destination of the shipment Your freight forwarder will then apply for the ECTN on your behalf.<br><br>Once approved, the ECTN will be valid for one year. If you have any questions about obtaining an ECTN, or about exporting from Madagascar in general, please contact us. We would be happy to assist you.', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(21, 'GUINEA BISSAU', 'guinea-bissau', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (21).svg', 'The Republic of Guinea-Bissau is located in West Africa. The country is bordered by Senegal to the north and Guinea to the south and east. Guinea-Bissau has a tropical climate with a rainy season from June to November. The country\'s economy is mostly based on agriculture. The main crops are rice, millet, peanuts, cashews, and timber. Fishing is also an important part of the economy. The official languages of Guinea-Bissau are Portuguese and African languages. The majority of the population is Muslim. The government of Guinea-Bissau is a republic.<br><br>The head of state is the President, who is elected by popular vote. The Prime Minister is the head of government and is appointed by the President. Guinea-Bissau is a member of the United Nations, the African Union, and the Economic Community of West African States.', 'ECTN Guinea Bissau | Seanautic Marine', 'The Republic of Guinea-Bissau is located in West Africa. The country is bordered by Senegal to the north and Guinea to the south and east. Guinea-Bissau has a tropical climate with a rainy season from June to November. The country\'s economy is mostly based on agriculture. The main crops are rice, millet, peanuts, cashews, and timber. Fishing is also an important part of the economy. The official languages of Guinea-Bissau are Portuguese and African languages. The majority of the population is Muslim. The government of Guinea-Bissau is a republic.<br><br>The head of state is the President, who is elected by popular vote. The Prime Minister is the head of government and is appointed by the President. Guinea-Bissau is a member of the United Nations, the African Union, and the Economic Community of West African States.', 'asset/maps/guinea-bissau.jpg', 'The Republic of Guinea-Bissau is a small country located in West Africa. Despite its small size, the country is rich in culture and history. For travellers, the most important thing to know about Guinea-Bissau is that it is one of the safest countries in Africa.<br><br>Guinea-Bissau is a Portuguese-speaking country, and the official language is Portuguese. However, there are many other languages spoken in the country, including Creole, French, and English. The best time to visit Guinea-Bissau is during the dry season, which runs from November to April. If you are planning to visit Guinea-Bissau, you will need to obtain a visa in advance. The process for getting a visa for Guinea-Bissau is relatively simple.<br><br>First, you will need to obtain a visa application form from the Guinea-Bissau consulate in your home country. Next, you will need to submit the completed visa application form, along with a passport-sized photo and the required fee. Once your application is processed, you will receive your visa. Guinea-Bissau is a beautiful country that is well worth a visit.', '<b>Do I require an ECTN for Guinea-Bissau and what is it?</b><br>For the export of certain items from the European Union, an ECTN, or Export Control Classification Number, is necessary (EU). Although Guinea-Bissau is not a member of the EU, it is nonetheless covered by the GSP, which implies that goods exported from the EU to Guinea-Bissau may be subject to ECTN requirements.', 'The Bill of Lading is needed.,,Business Invoice.,,Freight Bill (required if the freight amount is not specified on the commercial invoice).,,Export Declaration for Customs', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(22, 'LIBERIA', 'liberia', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (22).svg', 'The Republic of Liberia is a country on the West African coast. It is bordered by Sierra Leone to its west, Guinea to its north and Ivory Coast to its east. Liberia is the only African country that was never colonized by a European power. Liberia was founded in 1847 by free African Americans and ex-slaves from the United States. The capital city is Monrovia, which is named after James Monroe, the fifth President of the United States. Liberia is the world’s oldest republic and Africa’s first democratic republic. The country is rich in natural resources, with a tropical climate and diverse ecology. Liberia has a tropical rainforest climate with an average annual rainfall of over 4500 mm.<br><br>The country has a long coastline on the Atlantic Ocean, with some of the world’s best-surfing waves. Liberia also has large reserves of iron ore and timber. Liberia is a lower middle-income country with a GDP of US$1.8 billion in 2016. The country’s economy is primarily reliant on agriculture and mining. Liberia suffers from high levels of poverty and inequality.', 'ECTN Liberia | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Liberia: The Republic of Liberia is a country on the West African coast. It is bordered by Sierra Leone to its west, Guinea to its north and Ivory Coast to its east.', 'asset/maps/liberia.jpg', 'Ectn of Liberia The Government of Liberia has introduced a new electronic visa application system for nationals of eligible countries who wish to apply for a visa to enter Liberia. The electronic visa application system is designed to streamline the visa application process and improve customer service. All applications must be completed online and payments made using a credit or debit card.<br><br>The following documents are required to complete the online application: A passport with at least six months validity A passport-sized photograph A credit or debit card for payment Once the online application is complete, applicants will receive a confirmation email. They must then print out the confirmation email and present it, along with their passport, at a Liberian Diplomatic Mission when applying for their visa. The electronic visa application system is currently available for nationals of the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom.', '<b>Do I need to get an exit permit before leaving Liberia?</b><br><br>Yes, all travellers leaving Liberia are required to obtain an exit permit. Exit permits can be obtained from the Liberian Immigration Service or the Liberia National Police.<br><br><b>How do I get an exit permit?</b><br><br>Exit permits can be obtained from the Liberian Immigration Service or the Liberia National Police. You will need to submit a completed application form, your passport, and a photo.<br><br><b>How much does an exit permit cost?</b><br><br>The fee for an exit permit is $30.<br><br><b>How long is an exit permit valid?</b><br><br>An exit permit is valid for one year from the date of issuance.<br><br><b>Do I need to get an exit permit if I am leaving Liberia on a domestic flight?</b><br><br>No, you do not need to get an exit permit if you are leaving Liberia on a domestic flight.', 'The Bill of Lading.,,Business Invoice.,,Freight Bill (required if the freight amount is not specified on the commercial invoice).,,Export Declaration for Customs (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(23, 'SUDAN', 'sudan', '	\nasset/assets/flags/1 (16).svg', 'In October 2020, the government of Sudan introduced a new trade measure called the Electronic Cargo Tracking Note (ECTN). The ECTN is an electronic system that tracks the movement of cargo in and out of Sudan. The ECTN replaces the paper-based system that was previously in place. The ECTN is a requirement for all imported and exported goods and must be obtained prior to shipment.<br><br>The ECTN must be obtained from the designated Sudanese agency, which is the Sudanese Customs Authority. The ECTN system will help to streamline the movement of goods in and out of Sudan, and will provide Sudanese Customs with real-time information on the movement of cargo. The ECTN will also allow for the electronic tracking of payments made for goods imported into Sudan. The ECTN is a positive step forward for Sudan and will help to improve the efficiency of the country\'s trade.', 'ECTN Sudan | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Sudan: The ECTN is an electronic system that tracks the movement of cargo in and out of Sudan. Contact us Now.', 'asset/maps/sudan.jpg', 'Procedure for getting an ECTN of Sudan The first step is to complete an application form which can be obtained from the Directorate General of Customs.<br><br>The form must be signed by the applicant and the shipping company, and include the following information:<br>\r\n&#x2022; The applicant\'s name and address <br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of the shipping company <br>\r\n&#x2022; The name and address of the consignee -A description of the goods to be shipped <br>\r\n&#x2022; The estimated value of the goods  <br>\r\n&#x2022; The Harmonized System (HS) code of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; The route of the shipment<br><br>\r\nThe date of the shipment  Along with the completed application form, the following documents must also be submitted:<br>\r\n&#x2022; A letter of credit <br>\r\n&#x2022; A commercial invoice <br>\r\n&#x2022; A packing list <br>\r\n&#x2022; A bill of lading <br><br>\r\nAfter the application form and required documents have been submitted, the Directorate General of Customs will issue an ECTN which must be presented to the shipping company prior to the shipment of goods.', '<b>What details are necessary to receive an ECTN ?</b><br><br>The following details are needed in order to obtain an Ectn Sudan:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Shipper information <br>\r\n&#x2022; Consignee information <br>\r\n&#x2022; Notifier information <br>\r\n&#x2022; Bill of lading or air waybill number <br>\r\n&#x2022; Description of goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; HS code of goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; The net weight of goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Value of goods Online submission of the ECTN application is required at least 5 days before shipment. <br><br><b>How long does it take to receive an Ectn Sudan?</b><br><br>The ECTN can be obtained up to 3 days after the application has been filed.', 'Bill of Lading,,Commercial Invoice,,Freight Invoice (required if the freight amount is not specified on commercial invoice),,Customs Export Declaration (optional).', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL),
(24, 'LIBYA', 'libya', 'asset/assets/flags/1 (1).svg', 'The ECTN of LIBYA is a document that is required for all goods that are shipped to Libya. This document must be obtained before shipping and must be presented to the Libyan Customs Authorities upon arrival in Libya. The ECTN of LIBYA is issued by the Libyan Ministry of Economy and is valid for one year from the date of issue.', 'ECTN Libya | Seanautic Marine', 'ECTN Libya: The ECTN of LIBYA is a document that is required for all goods that are shipped to Libya. Contact us now.', 'asset/maps/libya.jpg', 'PROCEDURE FOR GETTING AN ECTN OF LIBYA If you are shipping goods to Libya, you must obtain an Export Control Transaction Number (ECTN) from the Libyan government.<br>The ECTN is a requirement for all exports to Libya and is obtained from the Libyan Ministry of Economy.<br>The ECTN application must be submitted online, and you will need the following information and documents to complete the application:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Detailed description of the goods to be exported <br>\r\n&#x2022; Value of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; HS code of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Country of origin of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Destination of the goods in Libya <br>\r\n&#x2022; Shipping route of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and address of the shipper <br>\r\n&#x2022; Name and address of the consignee <br><br>\r\nOnce the ECTN application is submitted, the Ministry of Economy will issue a unique ECTN number for your shipment. This number must be included on all shipping documents and presented to Libyan customs when the shipment arrives in the country.', '<b>What is an ECTN?</b><br><br>An ECTN is an export control document required for all cargo shipments to Libya.<br><br><b>How do I get an Ectn Libya?</b><br><br>You can apply for an ECTN through the Libyan embassy or consulate in your country, or a freight forwarder in Libya.', 'LIBYA - ECTN Certificate An ECTN ( Export Control Ticket Number) is required for all shipments of goods destined for Libya.<br>There are a few different types of ECTN that are required depending on the type of shipment:<br>\r\n&#x2022; DAP (Door-to-Airport) shipments require an ECTN for both the carrier and the shipper. <br>\r\n&#x2022;DAT (Door-to-Terminal) shipments require an ECTN for the shipper only. The ECTN must be obtained before shipment and must be included in the shipping documentation. <br><br>\r\nIf you are shipping DAP, you will need to provide the following information to obtain your ECTN:<br>\r\n&#x2022; Your company name and address -The name and address of the Libyan Consignee -A description of the goods being shipped -The value of the goods <br>\r\n&#x2022; The weight of the goods  <br>\r\n&#x2022; The shipment date -The expected arrival date in Libya If you are shipping DAT, you will need to provide the following information to obtain your ECTN:<br>\r\n -Your company name and address.', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', '2022-10-17 06:19:28.056190', NULL);

